...Get on the highway, I am doing the limit, the lights come on.  Al pulls over, cop passes him, gets behind me, I pull over.<br>
Cop comes to the window, &quot;Good morning.&quot;<br>
...Dave thinks &quot;It would be if I'd left work five minutes earlier, instead of sticking around to help out, and therefore crossing your path.&quot;  Dave says &quot;Hi.&quot;<br>
...Cop says &quot;Guess you know why I pulled you over.&quot;  Dave thinks &quot;Because you like brunettes?&quot;  Dave says, &quot;Yeah.&quot;<br>
...Cop says, &quot;Why ya got expired plates?&quot; <br>
...Dave thinks &quot;Does it matter?  Do you CARE that I've had moving expenses, hospital bills, an ailing grandmother to spend tons of money on, a jackass for a lawyer that calls me drunk off his ass at 11pm to return my calls?&quot;  Dave says &quot;You know, same stuff, different day.&quot;  Not that I want sympathy and understanding from this buzz cut Mike Ditka lookalike.  I just want him to finish his business, not make small talk, and go get the next lucky contestant in the grand game.<br>
...And so on.  AFTER I get back on the road, he follows me.  I set the cruise control at 58.  After a minute, lights come on again.  I'm thinking what the f$%#?  <br>
...Cop comes back, hands me my license.  &quot;Sorry to ruin your day, man.  You forgot this.&quot;  Sorry to ruin my day?   *I* forgot this???  Arg!  Ack!  Why don't you just shoot me in the foot, jackass, it would be less painful than spending a moment more in your presence!  <br>
...My nominee for the SASOB award for the day,  Sgt.  Nells!<br>
Who seems to think its my duty to remind him to give me my license back, who is sorry that he had to ruin my day, who looks like Mike Ditka, which is a crime in itself!  Runner up for the SASOB of the day award, Al the crazed hippie from hell, who was snickering like a jackass as he drove past me and Sgt. Nells.  I KNOW WHERE YOU WORK, assbag!<br>
...To the folks in coffeetalk, thanks for sharing my pain.  Even though I hate coffee.  Could we change this to &quot;Orange juice and bagels&quot; talk, or maybe even &quot;Bud Light talk&quot;?  No?  Eh, oh well, pass the coffee.<br>
<br>
Notu<br>
